309
00:21:26,924 --> 00:21:29,545
But what I tried to do here was lay out the clues

310
00:21:29,725 --> 00:21:31,146
and suggest certain feelings.

311
00:21:31,906 --> 00:21:35,407
I went about it by playing the game over and over and over

312
00:21:35,647 --> 00:21:37,548
with an open mind, each time trying

313
00:21:37,588 --> 00:21:39,448
to think of what details might be noticed.

314
00:21:40,563 --> 00:21:45,785
I was always trying to make connections, influence emotion, and insinuate that the characters

315
00:21:45,825 --> 00:21:49,366
are doing their own thing, and that the world is changing.

316
00:21:59,110 --> 00:22:04,452
So this neat little presentation may have made it seem like I knew what I was doing

317
00:22:04,572 --> 00:22:09,413
all along, but I want to assure you that at the time, I certainly did not feel that way.

318
00:22:10,534 --> 00:22:13,376
It was a learning process and it wasn't as succinct as this.

319
00:22:13,976 --> 00:22:16,958
And I say this to encourage you not to worry about that in yourselves.

320
00:22:17,479 --> 00:22:21,662
I was able to do this work just because I loved what I was doing and I loved this game

321
00:22:21,882 --> 00:22:25,905
